26 LC 112 4262
House Resolution 24EX
By: Representatives Lupton of the 83rd, Roberts of the 52nd, Lim of the 98th, and Tran of the
80th
A RESOLUTION
1 Recognizing and commending Medical Marijuana Therapeutics; and for other purposes.
2 WHEREAS, Medical Marijuana Therapeutics (MMT) is a Georgia-founded, family-owned
3 and operated medical cannabis practice led by a Georgia-licensed medical doctor and
4 dedicated to improving the quality of life for patients across the State of Georgia; and
5 WHEREAS, since 2019, MMT has distinguished itself as the gold standard in certification
6 services through its patient-centered approach to cannabis-focused medical care, providing
7 compassionate treatment, clinical professionalism, and ongoing support to individuals living
8 with complex and chronic medical conditions; and
9 WHEREAS, Dr. Madelaine Murad, the MMT Chief Medical Officer, has demonstrated a
10 deep commitment to individualized patient care by thoroughly reviewing each patient's
11 medical history, medications, and prior treatment experiences in order to develop thoughtful
12 cannabis treatment plans designed to support the best possible outcomes; and
13 WHEREAS, Vicki Jacobson, Chief Operating Officer and Practice Director of MMT, has
14 played an integral role in fostering a welcoming and supportive environment where patients
15 feel understood, respected, and cared for while also leading community outreach efforts,
H. R. 24EX
- 1 -

26 LC 112 4262
16 particularly among seniors, to increase awareness of the medical cannabis program and its
17 potential benefits; and
18 WHEREAS, Melanie Jacobson, the MMT Cannabis Consultant, has combined patient
19 advocacy, education, and personal understanding to help individuals throughout Georgia
20 navigate medical cannabis treatment with compassion, confidence, and ongoing support
21 aimed at improving quality of life; and
22 WHEREAS, MMT has prioritized the development of long-term doctor-patient relationships
23 grounded in trust, education, individualized care, and medical guidance tailored to each
24 patient's unique health needs; and
25 WHEREAS, MMT's medical doctor and cannabis consultant have been educated on and
26 remain informed by the latest clinical cannabis research so they are well equipped to advise
27 patients on cannabis products and provide comprehensive patient evaluations that include
28 education on cannabis medicine and the endocannabinoid system, medication interaction
29 reviews, guidance on products, formulations, delivery methods, and dosing, as well as
30 customized treatment plans designed to improve quality of life while emphasizing safe,
31 responsible, and therapeutic use; and
32 WHEREAS, MMT has expanded access to medical cannabis education and care through
33 statewide telemedicine services, helping patients throughout Georgia receive informed,
34 compassionate, and medically supervised support regardless of geographic barriers; and
35 WHEREAS, MMT has demonstrated a commitment to operating with integrity,
36 professionalism, and compliance with Georgia law while also serving as a strong advocate
H. R. 24EX
- 2 -

26 LC 112 4262
37 for patient education, access, and continued improvements to Georgia's Medical Cannabis
38 Program; and
39 WHEREAS, through its dedication to patient safety, medical education, ethical care
40 standards, and responsible cannabis guidance, MMT has helped establish greater confidence
41 and understanding surrounding medical cannabis treatment for patients and families across
42 the State of Georgia.
43 NOW, THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED BY THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES that
44 the members of this body recognize and commend Medical Marijuana Therapeutics for its
45 many outstanding contributions on behalf of the citizens of this state and extend best wishes
46 for continued success.
47 BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that the Clerk of the House of Representatives is authorized
48 and directed to make an appropriate copy of this resolution available for distribution to
49 Medical Marijuana Therapeutics.
